        "text": "Of the 104 patients who had received an ambulatory blood- pressure analysis during their follow-up period, 25 (18.4%) were hypertensive and receiving treatment for it. On Kaplan-Meier analysis of freedom from hypertension from the time of hospital discharge to date of last ambulatory blood-pressure measure- ment, there was no difference between the three weight groups (log-rankp = 0.39) (Fig. 3).",
